<CSSBackground-position-x>
<summary>
The <strong><c>background-position-x</c></strong> <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</see> property sets the initial horizontal position for each background image. The position is relative to the position layer set by <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-origin">background-origin</see>.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>EmbedInteractiveExample("pages/css/background-position-x.html")</para><para>The value of this property is overridden by any declaration of the <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background">background</see> or <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-position">background-position</see> shorthand properties applied to the element after it.</para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-position">background-position</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-position-y">background-position-y</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-position-inline">background-position-inline</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-position-block">background-position-block</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_backgrounds_and_borders/Using_multiple_backgrounds">Using multiple backgrounds</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/background-position-x"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</CSSBackground-position-x>
